unpack the cuon-xxx.tgz

go to dir cuon_client

on the client:
be root and type make install

on the client or server ( client/server) for install ZOPE and POSTGRES
edit Makefile to set server-Information
be root and type make install_server

make install_zope

Go with the Browser to your ZOPE-Site, login as Manager and
import Cuon.zexp and cuon_database_connection.zexp
update the extended Module for Zope

set up the enviroment-Variables:
      only Server  "export CUON_INI=/etc/cuon/cuon.ini "
      client und server "export CUON_HOME=~/cuon " 
      client und server "export CUON_SERVER=192.168.17.251:9673/Cuon ( in this example is IP_Adresse:Port/dir
      Client CUON_OOEXEC=/opt/OpenOffice.org1.1.0/program/python if you use Openoffice

 

edit cuon_database_connection and set the Values for your Postgres-Installation

On your client/server goto cuon_client and run 
sh pycuon server
choose Tools

then :

1.  choose SQL-SERVER
        db-check
        grants
    ( this will take some times )

2. choose XML-Tools
       load Defaults

okay,
now you can run /usr/bin/cuon 

Any Question :
